.TH "__devm_irq_alloc_descs" 9 "__devm_irq_alloc_descs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__devm_irq_alloc_descs \- Allocate and initialize a range of irq descriptors for a managed device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __devm_irq_alloc_descs
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "int irq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int from "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cnt "  ","
.BI "int node "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "const struct irq_affinity_desc *affinity "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to allocate the descriptors for
.IP "irq" 12
Allocate for specific irq number if irq >= 0
.IP "from" 12
Start the search from this irq number
.IP "cnt" 12
Number of consecutive irqs to allocate
.IP "node" 12
Preferred node on which the irq descriptor should be allocated
.IP "owner" 12
Owning module (can be NULL)
.IP "affinity" 12
Optional pointer to an irq_affinity_desc array of size \fIcnt\fP
which hints where the irq descriptors should be allocated
and which default affinities to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the first irq number or error code.
.SH "NOTE"
Use the provided wrappers (devm_irq_alloc_desc*) for simplicity.
